9. lusit: of light themes, in contrast to the seriousness of Stesi- chorus and the passion of Sappho. With this use of the word, cf. 1, 32, 2. —Anacreonz a native of Teos, who flourished in the second half of the sixth century ss.C. He re- sided at the court of Polycrates, tyrant of Samos, and later at that of Hipparchus in Athens. The extant collection of poems called Anacreontea are, however, of · Alexandrian origin.
